{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/19408", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/19408/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/19408/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/19408/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/19408", "id": 50443636, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWU1MDQ0MzYzNg==", "number": 19408, "title": "Incorrect Allowance Of Assignment Of Moved Variable (NoCopy)", "user": {"login": "mark3982", "id": 2837221, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjI4MzcyMjE=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2837221?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/mark3982", "html_url": "https://github.com/mark3982", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mark3982/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mark3982/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mark3982/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mark3982/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mark3982/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mark3982/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mark3982/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mark3982/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mark3982/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 1, "created_at": "2014-11-30T01:43:47Z", "updated_at": "2014-11-30T05:03:58Z", "closed_at": "2014-11-30T05:03:58Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "```\nuse std::kinds::marker::NoCopy;\n\nstruct FooNonCopyableNoCopy {\n    a:      uint,\n    b:      uint,\n    nocopy: NoCopy\n}\n\nimpl Clone for FooNonCopyableNoCopy {\n    fn clone(&self) -> FooNonCopyableNoCopy {\n        FooNonCopyableNoCopy { a: self.a + 1, b: self.b + 1, nocopy: NoCopy }\n    }\n}\n\nimpl FooNonCopyableNoCopy {\n    fn new(a: uint, b: uint) -> FooNonCopyableNoCopy {\n        FooNonCopyableNoCopy { a: a, b: b, nocopy: NoCopy }\n    }\n}\n\nfn consume(mut a: FooNonCopyableNoCopy) {\n    a.a = a.a + 1;    \n}\n\nfn bar(a: uint) {\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    let mut a: FooNonCopyableNoCopy = FooNonCopyableNoCopy::new(10, 11);\n\n    consume(a);\n\n    a.a = 3;\n\n    bar(a.a);\n} \n```\n\nIf you remove `bar(a.a)` it will compile. The machine code produced for the X86_64 target is actually passing a reference to `consume` which modifies it through the pointer, and then `a.a = 3` modifies the same stack instance (stack instance on main stack) but `bar(a.a)` errors on usage of moved value.\n\nI think it should disallow the assignment of `a.a = 3` because of `a` being moved.\n", "closed_by": {"login": "sfackler", "id": 1455697, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE0NTU2OTc=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1455697?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/sfackler", "html_url": "https://github.com/sfackler", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sfackler/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sfackler/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sfackler/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sfackler/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sfackler/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sfackler/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sfackler/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sfackler/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sfackler/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/19408/reactions", "t